### ZinTrust API - manual REST Client requests
### Requires VS Code extension: "REST Client" (humao.rest-client)
###
### 🔒 SECURITY ARCHITECTURE: Defense-in-Depth (10 Layers)
### ========================================================
### ZinTrust implements multiple independent security controls that each request must pass:
###
### Layer 1: Security Headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options)
### Layer 2: CORS (Origin validation, preflight handling)
### Layer 3: Rate Limiting (100 req/min baseline, stricter for auth/mutations)
### Layer 4: CSRF Protection (Double Submit Cookie pattern for state-changing requests)
### Layer 5: XSS Sanitization (Recursive HTML stripping via Xss.sanitize)
### Layer 6: Field Sanitization (Type-specific normalization via Sanitizer.*)
### Layer 7: Schema Validation (Type checking, format validation via Validator.validate)
### Layer 8: Authentication (JWT verification, session validation)
### Layer 9: Authorization (Role-based access control, ownership checks)
### Layer 10: SQL Injection Prevention (Prepared statements via QueryBuilder)
###
### 📝 Usage:
### 1) Start the dev server (default port is usually 7777):
###    zin start
### 2) Run "CSRF warmup" first (it captures cookies + CSRF token)
### 3) Run any POST/PUT requests after that
###
### 💡 Tip: If you want protected routes to succeed, set @jwt to a real token.
### You can mint a dev token with the CLI:
### zin jwt:dev --sub 1 --email dev@example.com --role admin
###
### 🧪 Security Testing:
### - Try requests WITHOUT CSRF token → Layer 4 blocks (403)
### - Try XSS payloads in body → Layer 5 sanitizes automatically
### - Try invalid schema data → Layer 7 rejects (422)
### - Try protected routes without JWT → Layer 8 blocks (401)
### - Try accessing other users' data → Layer 9 blocks (403)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:7777

